window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>How would spending a few extra days in each other’s company affect the relationship between Elizabeth Bennet and Mr Darcy? </p> <p>While her sister Jane is ill at Netherfield, Elizabeth overhears the proud Mr Darcy express his admiration of her and her fine eyes. Not sure what to think of his praise after all of their previous disagreements (and more flattered than she wants to admit) Elizabeth responds by teasing him, forcing Darcy to reconsider his opinion of a woman who has truly bewitched him.</p> <p>The ensuing day and weeks see confrontations and apologies and the beginnings of a friendship between Darcy and Elizabeth. But their warming acquaintance impacts the behavior of those around them inciting jealousy, anger and malicious falsehoods. Is the strength of their emotional connection enough to reunite them and put them back on the path to love?</p>"; 
